comment.narrative:
There is a need to advance the following type of green finance activities:                                                                                                                                                                                                    - supporting national green investments funds, such as the Senegal Strategic Investment Fund, FonSIS;
- capacity building for green finance, drawing on the experience of PAGE in cases like Mongolia;
- facilitating de-risking of public policy frameworks by revising and strengthening laws, regulations and related public incentives to allow for greater private sector investment in green sectors such as smart agriculture, fisheries, waste management, bio-trade, public procurement, with links to the 10-Year Framework Programme for Sustainable Consumption and Production;
- facilitating links between private sector technology supplier in line with green investment priorities;
- strengthening economic decision-making capacities including on addressing trade-offs and incentives.
